}} 'Cavite' (, (), is a province in the Philippines located on the southern
shores of Manila Bay in the CALABARZON region on Luzon island. It is one of
the most industrialized and one of the fastest growing provinces in the
country because of its close proximity to Metro Manila, located just south of
the capital.

The province is known as the Historical Capital of the Philippines. It was the
cradle of the Philippine Revolution, a renouncement of the Spanish colonial
control for over 300 years, culminating with the declaration of independence on
June 12, 1898 in Kawit, Cavite.
